an><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/6/01 5:22:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub73.ezboard.com/fsullonzektavernfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4028.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> An interesting tidbit of information</span><hr size=1> Some newts zone into Sro last night and we proceed to kill them.<br>
<br>
They went down really easy, didnt have sow or a druid with them that I saw - which was surprising to me. <br>
<br>
Nonetheless I found out something interesting.  Saii a newt monk, pulled the plug.  Now this part is a little unclear, but I am pretty sure that he pulled the plug then his toon FD'd on me, keeping my pet out of fight for a second anyhow. He was almost dead so I life tap him, up pops his toon, pet proceeds to kill the LD monk.<br>
<br>
Your pet has killed Saii!<br>
<br>
I couldnt loot him though, because he was LD.  But my pet finished him off - and today when I check the stat board, I got points for killing him.  <br>
<br>
Whats the use of pulling the plug in this case?  He dies, he loses xp (I think), I get points off him - why not fight it out till the end?  <br>
<br>
I am just glad he wasnt close enough to the zone to zone plug on me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/bsullonzektavern.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=spyder>Spyder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tavern Regular</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/6/01 5:27:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub73.ezboard.com/fsullonzektavernfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4028.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An interesting tidbit of information</span><hr size=1> Maybe he had alot of cash on him. /shrug<br>
<br>
Spyder <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/bsullonzektavern.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ergoyan>Ergoyan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tavern Regular</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/6/01 5:27:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub73.ezboard.com/fsullonzektavernfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4028.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Sometimes people go linkdead without pulling the plug. Maybe his isp dropped him. Or maybe, he wanted to hit for max damage that melees often do (because they are treated as an npc) when they go LD. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/uvigg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vigg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tavern Regular</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/6/01 5:30:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub73.ezboard.com/fsullonzektavernfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4028.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> i thought if you killed a LD you still got loot/points/insignia.  no? <p><img src="http://www.weeklyworldnews.com/imgs/batboy/batboy.jpg" width=144 height=144> a baby necro is born!!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/ufermundasz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FermundaSZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/6/01 5:32:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub73.ezboard.com/fsullonzektavernfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4028.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An interesting tidbit of information</span><hr size=1> No loot or insignia, but did get points.<br>
<br>
In all fairness, maybe he did get dropped - I dunno.<br>
<br>
I just wasnt expecting to get credited the kill since he was LD is all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/umarqussz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Marqus SZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tavern Regular</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/6/01 5:38:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub73.ezboard.com/fsullonzektavernfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4028.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An interesting tidbit of information</span><hr size=1> Back in the early days of the server people used to /q on me to try and get out of the exp death, as they could on test.  I still looted the insignia from the LD corpse so he was likely red or green to you...<br>
<br>
Or maybe since he was an npc the pets level was used as the check to allow the corpse to be looted..   doubt it though.<br>
<br>
I think you coned him when he was LD to be blue..   thats blue in NPC terms.  He was likely green in pc pvp terms. <p>Marqus<BR>
Darkenbane</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/utakish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Takish</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tavern Regular</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/6/01 5:38:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub73.ezboard.com/fsullonzektavernfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4028.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An interesting tidbit of information</span><hr size=1> I don't know why the monk would plug, except to save some coin.  Casters do it all the time to get npc melee skills. <p>Takish <BR>Dwarven Warrior<BR>Khin tells you: Are you high or something?</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/ufermundasz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FermundaSZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/6/01 5:50:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub73.ezboard.com/fsullonzektavernfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4028.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An interesting tidbit of information</span><hr size=1> I conned him before the plug Marqus and he conned even - I have heard that if you plug before dying you dont get looted, I thought that also meant they didnt get points for it.<br>
<br>
Let me rephrase I conned him before his untimely LD. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/utakish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Takish</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tavern Regular</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/6/01 5:56:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub73.ezboard.com/fsullonzektavernfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4028.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An interesting tidbit of information</span><hr size=1> Had to be something with the pet getting the kill I think.  At least as of a few weeks ago, you could loot coins and insignias from killing LD even cons.  I think Marqus is probably right, when LD it checks lvl of whatever got the killing blow (the pet lvl in this case). <p>Takish <BR>Dwarven Warrior<BR>Khin tells you: Are you high or something?</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/ufermundasz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FermundaSZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/6/01 5:58:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub73.ezboard.com/fsullonzektavernfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4028.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An interesting tidbit of information</span><hr size=1> Hmm, would make some sense I guess.  My pets are always blue to green to me - so given that if my pet was green to him there are no loot rights?<br>
<br>
Meaning if I kill a red con they lose xp and I get points but cannot loot them for insignia? Is that correct? <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub73.ezboard.com/fsullonzektavernfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=4028.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub73.ezboard.com/fsullonzektavernfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=4028.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub73.ezboard.com/fsullonzektavernfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4028.topic&index=9><img src=http://home.att.net/~neoleo/reply2.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub73.ezboard.com/fsullonzektavernfrm1.threadControl?topicID=4028.topic><img src= border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub73.ezboard.com/fsullonzektavernfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4028.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub73.ezboard.com/fsullonzektavernfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4028.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub73.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="sullonzektavernfrm1">General Discussion<option value="sullonzektavernfrm2">Marketplace<option value="sullonzektavernfrm3">No Holds Barred<option value="sullonzektavernfrm4">Guilds of Sullon Zek<option value="sullonzektavernfrm5">Roleplay<option value="sullonzektavernfrm6">Testing Grounds<option value="sullonzektavernfrm7">Administration Station</select></td><td><input type=submit value="Go" class=inputbutton></td></